I"&<p>Circa 150 homes have been earmarked for potential demolition at the Sutton Court estate.</p>

<p>The Sutton Court estate is one of seven estates listed in <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MdX6GlaHDoBdG6CTsvjFaIuPtIa9id5O/view">Sutton’s Local Plan (2018)</a> for potential redevelopment:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonplan.png" class="img-fluid rounded img-thumbnail" /></p>

<p>It is also earmarked in Sutton’s <a href="http://sutton.addresscafe.com/app/exploreit/">Policy Map</a> as a potential renewal area:</p>

<p><img src="/images/suttonpolicymap.png" class="img-fluid rounded img-thumbnail" /></p>

<p>The estate is close to the train station and comprises six 3-storey blocks and two 7-storey blocks of flats set around generous areas of green space, trees and a games court.</p>

